<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-126-998  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 126 998.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDN  Jan 25 1990 v35 n2A p1(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>For a change of pace, try pacemaker design.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Stenzler-Centonze, Marjorie.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Pacemaker manufacturers are hiring electrical engineers (EEs) tocreate a new generation of products.andP;  Industry consolidation hascreated a need for EEs.andP;  Prior medical electronics experience isgenerally not a hiring requirement.andP;  Manufacturers need EEs with arange of talents to design a variety of products.andP;  Medtronic Incof Minneapolis is hiring computer scientists and softwareengineers.andP;  Large pacemaker companies will benefit fromimplantable defibrillation technology but smaller companies mustrely on more profitable areas.andP;  While some companies find thepacemaker industry static, a ZMI Corp spokesperson says businessis growing.andP;  ZMI is hiring analog and digital designers andsoftware engineers to develop temporary pacemakers which areattached externally.andP;  Many other challenging opportunities existin the pacemaker industry.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     DesignMedical ResearchResearch and DevelopmentRecruitmentProduct DevelopmentElectrical Engineering.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>